"{\"_values\": {\"description\": \"The ex-cop will be held at Oak Park Heights until he\\u2019s sentenced in June. \", \"author\": \"Jemima McEvoy\", \"url\": \"https://www.forbes.com/sites/jemimamcevoy/2021/04/21/derek-chauvin-transferred-to-minnesota-maximum-security-prison-after-murder-conviction/\", \"title\": \"Derek Chauvin Transferred To Minnesota Maximum-Security Prison After Murder Conviction\", \"content\": [\"Former Minneapolis Police Officer Derek Chauvin was transferred to the state\\u2019s only Level 5 Maximum-security prison after he was found guilty of murdering George Floyd by a jury on Tuesday evening.\\u00a0\", \"\\u201cOak Park Heights is the highest custody level in the Minnesota DOC system,\\u201d the Minnesota Department of Corrections\\u2019 website reads. \\u201cHowever, the majority of inmates housed here are maximum and close custody, as some of the inmates need a higher level of security.\\u201d\\u00a0\", \"It\\u2019s unclear how much jail time Chauvin will face when he\\u2019s sentenced as Minnesota sentencing guidelines recommend a median sentence of 12.5 years for both murder counts and four years for the manslaughter charge for those with no criminal history. However, prosecutors have indicated they plan to advocate for a higher than recommended prison term because of \\u201caggravating factors\\u201d in the case, including that the crime happened in front of a child and that Floyd was treated with \\u201cparticular cruelty.\\u201d If aggravating factors are present, the maximum sentences would be 40 years for second-degree murder, 25 years for third-degree murder and 10-years for second-degree manslaughter.\\u00a0\", \"Chauvin\\u2019s defense team are likely to appeal the verdict, arguing the officer wasn\\u2019t given a fair trial due to the high-profile nature of the case. Chauvin\\u2019s attorneys have to notify the court within 60 days if they plan to appeal.\\u00a0\", \" (Forbes)\"], \"num\": 17}}"